          "kind": "numeric",
          "text": "A cemetery that otherwise complies with this section may be designated an endowment care cemetery even though it contains a small area that may be sold without endowed care, if it is separately set off from the remainder of the cemetery. The head of all contracts and certificates of ownership or deeds referring to plots in this area must contain the phrase nonendowed care in at least 10-point black type.",
          "subsections": []
        },
        {
          "label": "(13)",
          "token": "13",
          "kind": "numeric",
          "text": "A nonendowed care cemetery is a cemetery that does not deposit in an endowment care fund the minimum amounts specified in subsection",
